iGetEntryByKey

ViewEntry iGetEntryByKey(java.util.Vector paramVector,
                         boolean paramBoolean,
                         int paramInt)
This method is neccessary to get some Backend-functions working.
Attention: The name of the function seems not to be important, but the position! It seems that the backendbridge calls the n-th. method in this class. (didn't figure out, how n was computed. Method is at lotus.domino.local.View.class.getDeclaredMethods()[68], but 68 has no correlation to thisClass.getDeclaredMethods )
To find the correct positon, trace a call of
DominoUtils.getViewEntryByKeyWithOptions(view, "key", 2243)
and hit "step into" until you are in one of the mehtods of this file. Move this mehtod to the position you found with the debugger.

getAllDocuments

public DocumentCollection getAllDocuments()
Description copied from interface: View
Gets all documents from the View.

NOTE: This doesn't take into account any searching done over the view. It also iterates the NoteIDs from the entries in the view and adds those documents to a collection. Although a convenience method, in all likelihood the recommended approach would be to use getAllEntries and then, while iterating the entries, call getDocument().

One use case for this is if you need to pass a DocumentCollection to a method, e.g. org.openntf.domino.helpers.DocumentSyncHelper.process(DocumentCollection)

Specified by:
getAllDocuments in interface View
Returns:
DocumentCollection
